      " sorry\n\n/-\nA bird `S` is called a *starling* if for any three birds `x`, `y`, `z`, the following holds:\n`(((S ◁ x) ◁ y) ◁ z) = (x ◁ z) ◁ (y ◁ z)`.\n-/\n\n-- the definition of a starling\nnoncomputable abbrev is_starling (S : Bird) := sorry\n\n/-\nThe following code proves various properties about these birds.\n-/\n\nnamespace EnchantedForest.Introduction\n\n/-\nThe *identity bird* `I` is a bird that, when called, responds with the name of the bird that called it.\nIn other words, for any bird `x`, `I ◁ x = x`.\n-/\n\n-- the definition of the identity bird\nnoncomputable abbrev I : Bird := sorry\n\n/-\nA bird `A` is called *egocentric* if its response to any other bird `x` is itself.\nIn other words, `A` is egocentric if `∀ x, A ◁ x = A`.\n-/\n\n-- the definition of an egocentric bird\nnoncomputable abbrev is_egocentric (A : Bird) := sorry\n\n/-\nA bird `A` is called *fond* of another bird `B` if `A`'s response to `B` is `B`.\nIn other words, `A` is fond of `B` if `A ◁ B = B`.\n-/\n\n-- the definition of a fond bird\nnoncomputable abbrev is_fond_of (A B : Bird) := sorry\n\n/-\nA bird `A` is called *fixated* on another bird `B` if `A`'s response to any other bird `x` is `B`.\nIn other words, `A` is fixated on `B` if `∀ x, A ◁ x = B`.\n-/\n\n-- the definition of a fixated bird\nnoncomputable abbrev is_fixated_on (A B : Bird) := sorry\n\n/-\nA bird `A` is called *hopelessly egocentric* if it is egocentric and also fond of itself.\nIn other words, `A` is hopelessly egocentric if `A` is egocentric (`∀ x, A ◁ x = A`) and also `A` is fond of `A` (`A ◁ A = A`).\n-/\n\n-- the definition of a hopelessly egocentric bird\nnoncomputable abbrev is_hopelessly_egocentric (A : Bird) := sorry\n\n/-\nA pair of birds `(A, B)` is called *agreeable* if there exists some bird `x` such that their responses to `x` are the same.\nIn other words, `(A, B)` is agreeable if `∃ x, A ◁ x = B ◁ x`.\n-/\n\n-- the definition of an agreeable pair of birds\nnoncomputable abbrev is_agreeable_pair (A B : Bird) := sorry\n\n/-\nA bird `A` is called *agreeable* if it forms an agreeable pair with every other bird `B`.\nIn other words, `A` is agreeable if `∀ B, ∃ x, A ◁ x = B ◁ x`.\n-/\n\n-- the definition of an agreeable bird\nnoncomputable abbrev is_agreeable (A : Bird) := sorry\n\n/-\nA bird `K` is called a *kestrel* if for any two birds `x` and `y`, the response of `K` to `x` when `y` is called is `x`.\nIn other words, `K` is a kestrel if `∀ x y, (K ◁ x) ◁ y = x`.\n-/\n\n-- the definition of a kestrel\nnoncomputable abbrev is_kestrel (K : Bird) := sorry\n\n/-\nA bird `M` is called a *mockingbird* if its response to any bird `x` is the response of `x` to itself.\nIn other words, `M` is a mockingbird if `∀ x, M ◁ x = x ◁ x`.\n-/\n\n-- the definition of a mockingbird\nnoncomputable abbrev is_mockingbird (M : Bird) := sorry\n\n/-\nA bird `B` is called a *bluebird* if for any three birds `x`, `y`, `z`, the following holds:\n`(((B ◁ x) ◁ y) ◁ z) = x ◁ (y ◁ z)`.\n-/\n\n-- the definition of a bluebird\nnoncomputable abbrev is_bluebird (B : Bird) := sorry\n\n/-\nA bird `L` is called a *lark* if for any two birds `x` and `y`, the following holds:\n`(L ◁ x) ◁ y = x ◁ (y ◁ y)`.\n-/\n\n-- the definition of a lark\nnoncomputable abbrev is_lark (L : Bird) := sorry\n\n/-\nA bird `S` is called a *starling* if for any three birds `x`, `y`, `z`, the following holds:\n`(((S ◁ x) ◁ y) ◁ z) = (x ◁ z) ◁ (y ◁ z)`.\n-/\n\n-- the definition of a starling\nnoncomputable abbrev is_starling (S : Bird) := sorry\n\n/-\nThe following code proves various properties about these birds.\n-/\n\nnamespace EnchantedForest.Introduction\n\n/-\nThe *identity bird* `I` is a bird that, when called, responds with the name of the bird that called it.\nIn other words, for any bird `x`, `I ◁ x = x`.\n-/\n\n-- the definition of the identity bird\nnoncomputable abbrev I : Bird := sorry\n\n/-\nA bird `A` is called *egocentric* if its response to any other bird `x` is itself.\nIn other words, `A` is egocentric if `∀ x, A ◁ x = A`.\n-/\n\n-- the definition of an egocentric bird\nnoncomputable abbrev is_egocentric (A : Bird) := sorry\n\n/-\nA bird `A` is called *fond* of another bird `B` if `A`'s response to `B` is `B`.\nIn other words, `A` is fond of `B` if `A ◁ B = B`.\n-/\n\n-- the definition of a fond bird\nnoncomputable abbrev is_fond_of (A B : Bird) := sorry\n\n/-\nA bird `A` is called *fixated* on another bird `B` if `A`'s response to any other bird `x` is `B`.\nIn other words, `A` is fixated on `B` if `∀ x, A ◁ x = B`.\n-/\n\n-- the definition of a fixated bird\nnoncomputable abbrev is_fixated_on (A B : Bird) := sorry\n\n/-\nA bird `A` is called *hopelessly egocentric* if it is egocentric and also fond of itself.\nIn other words, `A` is hopelessly egocentric if `A` is egocentric (`∀ x, A ◁ x = A`) and also `A` is fond of `A` (`A ◁ A = A`).\n-/\n\n-- the definition of a hopelessly egocentric bird\nnoncomputable abbrev is_hopelessly_egocentric (A : Bird) := sorry\n\n/-\nA pair of birds `(A, B)` is called *agreeable* if there exists some bird `x` such that their responses to `x` are the same.\nIn other words, `(A, B)` is agreeable if `∃ x, A ◁ x = B ◁ x`.\n-/\n\n-- the definition of an agreeable pair of birds\nnoncomputable abbrev is_agreeable_pair (A B : Bird) := sorry\n\n/-\nA bird `A` is called *agreeable* if it forms an agreeable pair with every other bird `B`.\nIn other words, `A` is agreeable if `∀ B, ∃ x, A ◁ x = B ◁ x`.\n-/\n\n-- the definition of an agreeable bird\nnoncomputable abbrev is_agreeable (A : Bird) := sorry\n\n/-\nA bird `K` is called a *kestrel* if for any two birds `x` and `y`, the response of `K` to `x` when `y` is called is `x`.\nIn other words, `K` is a kestrel if `∀ x y, (K ◁ x) ◁ y = x`.\n-/\n\n-- the definition of a kestrel\nnoncomputable abbrev is_kestrel (K : Bird) := sorry\n\n/-\nA bird `M` is called a *mockingbird* if its response to any bird `x` is the response of `x` to itself.\nIn other words, `M` is a mockingbird if `∀ x, M ◁ x = x ◁ x`.\n-/\n\n-- the definition of a mockingbird\nnoncomputable abbrev is_mockingbird (M : Bird) := sorry\n\n/-\nA bird `B` is called a *bluebird* if for any three birds `x`, `y`, `z`, the following holds:\n`(((B ◁ x) ◁ y) ◁ z) = x ◁ (y ◁ z)`.\n-/\n\n-- the definition of a bluebird\nnoncomputable abbrev is_bluebird (B : Bird) := sorry\n\n/-\nA bird `L` is called a *lark* if for any two birds `x` and `y`, the following holds:\n`(L ◁ x) ◁ y = x ◁ (y ◁ y)`.\n-/\n\n-- the definition of a lark\nnoncomputable abbrev is_lark (L : Bird) := sorry\n\n/-\nA bird `S` is called a *starling* if for any three birds `x`, `y`, `z`, the following holds:\n`(((S ◁ x) ◁ y) ◁ z) = (x ◁ z) ◁ (y ◁ z)`.\n-/\n\n-- the definition of a starling\nnoncomputable abbrev is_starling (S : Bird) := sorry\n\n/-\nThe following code proves various properties about these birds.\n-/\n\nnamespace EnchantedForest.Introduction\n\n/-\nThe *identity bird* `I",
      "\n    intro x\n    have h2 : ∀ (y : Bird), (K ◁ x) y = x := by\n      intro y\n      apply K.call\n    have h3 : x ◁ (K ◁ x) = K ◁ x := by\n      have h4 : (K ◁ x) is a bird := by\n        exact K ◁ x\n      have h5 : ∀ (y : Bird), (K ◁ x) y = x := by\n        intro y\n        apply K.call\n      have h10 : (K ◁ x) = (fun (_ : Bird) => x) := by\n        funext y\n        simpa using K.call\n      rw [h10]\n      all_goals simp\n    exact h3",
